{
  "message": "fuzz(block-mem-io-engine): 24 structured seeds across batch shapes\n\nExisting 10 seeds left batched IoOp combinations sparsely covered.\nAdd 24 seeds spanning the engine's operational surface:\n\n  memory sizes: 0 (degenerate), 64, 128, 256, 512, 1024, 4096 (max)\n\n  per-batch op shapes:\n    * empty batch (no ops)\n    * sync-only (1 / 24 syncs in one batch)\n    * single read / write at boundary, beyond capacity, zero-length\n    * write-then-read identity verification\n    * journal pattern: write \u2192 sync \u2192 read\n    * many-small-write fill (16 \u00d7 4-byte writes spanning 64B mem)\n    * all-reads / all-writes batches (no mixing)\n    * mixed batch with interleaved sync\n\n  multi-batch sequences:\n    * 4 batches each writing a quadrant + final read\n    * 4 batches with sync between (stats.batches accumulator)\n\n  error-path coverage:\n    * mem=0 with operations (every op errors)\n    * read past memory end / offset > capacity (slack-bounded)\n    * write at offset+len == capacity (boundary success)\n    * read of unwritten region (returns zeros)\n\n314K runs / 11s post-seed surface no crashes.",
